#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:1
msgid "How to write a tutorial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:3
msgid "This is a guide to writing tutorials about Nix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:5
msgid ""
"By tutorials we mean *lessons* as described in the [Diátaxis framework for "
"technical documentation](https://diataxis.fr/), and recommend becoming "
"familiar with Diátaxis before proceeding. Especially note [the difference "
"between tutorials and guides](https://diataxis.fr/tutorials-how-to/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:8
msgid "Target audience"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:10
msgid ""
"The main target audience of Nix tutorials are software developers with at "
"least basic experience on the Linux command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:12
msgid ""
"Experts answering questions immediately, personalised instructions and "
"training, and other forms of apprenticeship are known to be the most "
"effective support for learning Nix. **These tutorials are targeted at those "
"who don't have access to any of that**, and should therefore be written to "
"be suitable for self-directed learning. This is achieved by following the "
"structure outlined here, which is primarily characterised by aiming to avoid "
"and close all information gaps for the learner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:16
msgid ""
"As a byproduct, a well-written tutorial will be useful as lecture notes for "
"use in interactive training sessions. Therefore, the secondary target "
"audience are instructors teaching Nix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:19
msgid "Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:21
msgid ""
"Writing a high-quality tutorial takes some time – for you and others. Most "
"of that time is typically spent collaboratively:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:23
msgid "Figuring out the right approach"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:24
msgid ""
"Ensuring that the instructions are neither too sparse nor too dense for "
"learners"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:25
msgid "Finding ever-more succinct and clear ways to convey ideas"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:27
msgid "Follow these steps to avoid redoing work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:29
msgid "Pick a topic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:31
msgid ""
"There is a [tracking issue](https://github.com/NixOS/nix.dev/issues/572) for "
"tutorials that the documentation team has decided should exist as part of "
"the tutorial series. Pick an issue that covers a topic that you're either "
"knowledgeable about or have a particular interest in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:34
msgid ""
"Check referenced issues and pull requests to make sure you won't duplicate "
"work that someone else has already started!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:36
msgid ""
"There are more [tutorial requests](https://github.com/NixOS/nix.dev/issues?"
"q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3Atutorial) than captured in the outline. [Open "
"a new issue](https://github.com/NixOS/nix.dev/issues/new?&template=tutorial."
"md) if what you wanted to work on isn't tracked anywhere. This is an "
"opportunity for you to clarify your goals, and an opportunity for everyone "
"else to find out that there's interest in that subject."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:40
msgid "Submit a pull request with an outline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:42
msgid ""
"Submit a pull request with an outline of the tutorial following [our "
"recommended structure](#structure). The outline should contain bullet points "
"on each section's content. Reference the tracking issue from the pull "
"request description to announce that you're working on a tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:46
msgid ""
"A review will ensure you're going in the right direction in terms of "
"learning objectives and technical implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:48
msgid "Expand on the outline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:50
msgid ""
"Elaborate the contents of the tutorial following your outline and the []"
"(style-guide)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:52
msgid ""
"A review will ensure that you get all the required information in the right "
"order without overwhelming learners."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:54
msgid "Follow up on review comments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:56
msgid ""
"Revise your tutorial based on the detailed feedback. We recommend testing "
"your tutorial with friends or coworkers. This will both help with revealing "
"implicit prerequisites as well as provide a realistic estimate of the "
"reading time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:60
msgid "A final review will check that everything is technically correct."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:62
msgid "Structure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:64
msgid "Each tutorial should answer the following questions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:66
msgid ""
"In addition, we strongly recommend the book [How Learning Works (summary)]"
"(https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/mAdMkFqWzbJRB544m/book-review-how-learning-"
"works) as a guide for designing learning materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:68
msgid "What will you learn?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:70
msgid "Describe the problem statement and learning goals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:72
msgid ""
"The learning goal of a tutorial is always acquiring a skill, which is "
"distinguished by being applicable to a set of situations with recurrent "
"patterns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:74
msgid "What do you need?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:76
msgid ""
"State the prerequisite knowledge and skills. The tutorial should always be "
"written such that the stated prerequisites are sufficient to achieve the "
"learning goals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:79
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:81
msgid "links to previous chapters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:82
msgid "domain-specific skills or knowledge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:84
msgid "How long does it take?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:86
msgid ""
"Estimate the reading time. This is important for learners to make sure they "
"have the capacity to achieve the planned tasks and thus avoid frustration "
"that may prevent them from continuing on their journey into the Nix "
"ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:89
msgid ""
"The estimate will depend on the learner's pre-existing knowledge and "
"proficiency. You can note how optional skills or knowledge may influence "
"reading time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:92
msgid "What to do?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:94
msgid ""
"Provide steps to achieve the learning goal. These should take the form of "
"direct instructions which repeatably lead to the desired outcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:97
msgid ""
"It is also worthwhile to add contextual explanations within `:::{dropdown}` "
"blocks. This can help with understanding while keeping distractions minimal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:100
msgid "What did you learn?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:102
msgid ""
"Provide exercises or worked examples, and other means of self-assessment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:104
msgid ""
"This is also a good place to offer the readers ways to give feedback or ask "
"the authors questions in order to continue improving the tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:106
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:108
msgid "Depending on how well a use case is explored, point the reader to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:110
msgid "reference manuals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:111
msgid "guides or other tutorials"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:112
msgid "links to known-good external resources, with summaries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:113
msgid ""
"overview of available support tools, and their state of maturity and "
"maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:114
msgid "overview of ideas, and the state of community discussion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:116
msgid ""
"We recommend making an explicit separation of practical from theoretical "
"learning resources, as then readers will be able to quickly decide to either "
"get things done or learn more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/writing-a-tutorial.md:118
msgid ""
"External resources should have a summary to set expectations, ideally "
"including reading time. Blog posts should have their original title in the "
"link, and `(<author>, <year>)`: Give authors credit, give readers an idea of "
"how up to date the information is."
msgstr ""
